1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:04,500
Introducing Pangolin — built for the Sola Security Hackathon

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,500
Sola's pipeline scans your GitHub workflows daily,
classifying findings and alerting your team

3
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:16,000
Our CLI pulls data from Sola MCP — the regex engine
scans 105 workflows in 0.1 seconds

4
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:21,000
Then GPT-5.5 goes deep — reasoning through
real attack chains

5
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:27,500
6 confirmed vulnerabilities, 0 false positives,
29 proof-of-concept files generated

6
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:33,500
The report shows severity breakdown, attack scenarios,
and downloadable PoC files

7
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:42,000
Detection isn't enough — one command generates
a fix and opens a GitHub PR

8
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:47,500
Full vulnerability context and clean diff

9
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:55,500
Everything flows to Slack — alerts, reports,
fix notifications. A complete security loop.

10
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:59,500
Pangolin. Scan. Analyze. Fix. Automatically.
